{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> πηλός</b> <br /> (<i>Doric dialect</i> <b>πᾱλός</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophron Comicus 32, 3rd c.BC: Cercidas Iambographus 3.3, “IG” 5(1).1447.16 (Messene, 3rd-2nd c.BC)), ὁ, Syrac. ἡ 2nd c.AD: Phrynichus Atticista 38\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]:— <b>clay, earth</b>, used by masons and potters, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.36, 136, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Aves” 1143, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.76, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Theaetetus” 147a, 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 15.35.2; πηλὸν ὀργάζειν 5th c.BC: Eupolis Comicus 248, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Fragmenta” 482, compare 510, 787, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Aves” 839 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; π. ἠχυρωμένος <b>clay</b> mixed with chaff for use as mortar, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “IG” 22.463.42, compare 5(1)[same place], LXX.Gen.11.3 \">LXX</a>]; εὐώδεϊ πηλῷ, of <b>earth</b> on which wine has been poured, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd-4th c.AD: Tryphiodorus Epicus 349 \">Refs 3rd c.AD+</a>]; Βρομιώδεα π. φύρησαν.. Χάριτες, of a drinkingcup, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"“Anthologia Graeca” 11.27 (1st c.AD(?): Macedonius Epigrammaticus)\">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]: <i>metaphorically</i>, <b>clay</b> from which man was made: hence ὁ π. ὁ Προμηθεῖος, of man, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Callimachus Epicus “Fragmenta” 87, compare 133, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Aves” 686; ἐκ ποίου πηλοῦ πεφύρητ᾽ εἰδότα 3rd c.BC: Herodas Mimographus 2.29. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>mud, mire</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.5, 4.28, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Vespae” 248, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.4, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 363d, etc.: proverbial, ἔξω κομίζειν πηλοῦ πόδα 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Choephori” 697 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; κάσις πηλοῦ ξύνουρος, i. e. dust, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Ag.” 495: _metaphorically_, ἀνέρες ὧν τὸ κέαρ παλῶ σέσακται 3rd c.BC: Cercidas Iambographus [prev. cited] \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> poetical, <b>thick</b> or <b>muddy wine, lees</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Fragmenta” 783 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of wine spilt on the floor, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.463a, 2nd c.AD(?): Charito Scriptor Eroticus 1.3 \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]; compare Πηλεύς near the end <br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <i>metaphorically</i>, <b>dolt, blockhead, Comedy texts Adesp.</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 890. \">Refs</a>]","strongNumber":"G4081","accentedUnicode":"πηλός","shortDef":"mud, lump of clay","mediumDef":"mud, lump of clay <br /><b>moist earth, mud, slime,</b> <ref='Jhn.9.6, 11, 14, 15'>Jn. 9:6, 11, 14, 15</ref>; <b>clay,</b> potter's <b>clay,</b> <ref='Rom.9.21'>Rom. 9:21</ref>*","stepGloss":"clay","stepTransliteration":"pēlos","count":6,"_es_Definition":"barro, lodo ; arcilla","_zh_tw_Definition":"1) 陶匠用的黏土 (羅9:21)<br>2) 泥濘,泥沼","_zh_Definition":"1) 陶匠用的黏土 (罗9:21)<br>2) 泥泞,泥沼","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"đất sét; bùn.","_zh_tw_Gloss":"泥","_es_Gloss":"arcilla","_zh_Gloss":"泥"}]}